{"key":"post-9542978","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9542978</id>\n<content>One should not waste time making LC unless the culture has been proved on agar first, and then blended in an Eberbach.&amp;nbsp; Since the setup costs are so high, I routinely advise against making liquid cultures.&amp;nbsp; Once you have an Eberbach and clean cultures on petri dishes, you blend the contents of the dish up into the sterile water and malt.&amp;nbsp; The 500 ml of liquid culture is then ready for use 5 to 7 days later.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9548555</next>\n<prev>9541931</prev>\n<first>9541931</first>\n<last>9550269</last>\n<when>1231089891</when>\n<utime>01/04/09 07:24 PM</utime>\n</post>"}